text:
for all the #notallmen who still don’t get it, today i parked about 50m further away from my work than i could have because the closest available park was next to a van. yes it’s only 50m, but it was barely even a conscious decision. these are the choices women make everyday in an attempt to not get raped and killed. these are things we are advised to do to stay safe. help solve this problem by educating the men around you; your sons, your brothers, your mates, your fathers, your uncles. no means no. you are not entitled to affection. women deserve to be feel safe and respected. #thingswomendotostaysafe #metoo #metoomovement #bethesolution

and as a preemptive strike to those who are arguing ‘you can’t even flirt with women today, the world is too pc!’ i say this. you can still flirt, you can still ask a woman out, or ask her if she would like to join you for a drink, just do it respectfully (don’t just start groping her because that’s assault) and instead of getting angry or offended if she declines, accept it and walk away.

text:
hope’s direction is to assist survivors with self-esteem. the very essence of a person, the very thing that can, once damaged, have a detrimental effect on a person’s ability to see their self-worth. at hope retreats, survivors will encounter a holistic approach to actively acquiring the right tools to assist them re-build a positive self-esteem and thus a positive self-worth.

hope’s main purpose is to concentrate on the survivor at the end of their battle. hope retreats will be the prize for lack of a better word, the reward for surviving the harshness of coming forward, speaking up, cementing charges, going through the court cases. research shows us that while there is assistance after coming forward and during the process, there is nothing to assist with further recovery thereafter. 
#metoo #believesurvivors #womenpower #inspiringwomen #ruok #helpingothers #givinghope #makingthemwarriors #fightingback

text:
sasha believes it is important the students of wwu have a voice. 
meet nicole- the vice president of the club sasha. she is currently running for the as senate on a platform of doing more for survivors. nicole describes why sasha was something she felt was important to be apart of. 
nicole: “through my research into sexual violence at wwu the human services program, i learned that the administration at western washington university does an extremely poor job of prioritizing the emotional and physical wellbeing of survivors over that of perpetrators. i also learned that the administration does an equally poor job at involving students in policy-making and sanctioning, and that decision-making power is concentrated in the hands of very few. that is why i chose to become involved with sasha -- wwu needs a group of informed, educated students to act not only as a voice for survivors, but to hold the administration accountable for the harm they have caused.”
.
.
.
.

#facesofwwu #wwu #westernwashingtonuniversity #wwubound #sexualassault #sexualharassment #survivor #metoo #metoomovement #believesurvivors #changetheculture

text:
a piece from photobook 'celestial bodies' by young artists @eleanorhardwick @rachelhardwickphotography and @chrissiewhite offers a new perspective on the often hyper-sexualised female body: ⭐️
“in society and the media, the female body seems to be either hyper-sexualised or shamed, and rarely appreciated for the incredible feat of nature that it really is. i think that presenting the female form as somewhat other-worldly and alien, all preconceptions that many of us have linked to the idea of the nude body are stripped away. by looking at it with fresh eyes, within the context of landscapes that almost look as if they could be on another planet, we are able to take a step back and view the world from a new perspective.” 👄 @rachelhardwickphotography .
.
.
.
.
.
.

text:
i will never forget the feelings and thoughts i had when i was hit with anxiety and depression... at the time it came out of nowhere. in hindsight, it had been trying to get my attention for a long time...
.
'im going crazy, they are going to lock me up, im a hazard to my kids, im screwed forever, i cant live like this'. this was my constant inner dialogue... for atleast a year whilst i was in the thick of it... my mind was all screwed up... my mind... i had to fix my mind.. hindsight is wonderful isnt it! how much i have come to know. .
if up to 90% seretonin is produced in the gut, is your low mood still your mind?
.
if depression is a common symptom of a thyroid imbalance, is that in the mind?
.
if high copper and low zinc levels levels increase anxiety... is that all  in the mind?
.
you are not broken my sweet soul. you heart can heal, your light can shine again. depression and anxiety are a symptom of something much deeper. these symptoms dont need to be lifelong sentences i promise you! and there is never a full stop or end to healing. there are so many avenues to really get to the cause of whats triggering your symptoms and really heal. if you want to talk it out, give me a call! be well beautiful. charmaine xxx

text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
yesterday, 22 november, the #safecitiesforwomen network, and the transport company (bor kor sor) held a press conference, “bor kor sor butts in: make buses safe from sexual harassment” unveiling a training program and handbook for employees of the bus operator in order to help #sexualharassment victims and deal with perpetrators. ✊🏼
five months in the making, the joint action between one of thailand’s biggest bus operators and the safe cities for women network is the first concrete cooperative effort between civil society and a public transport service in putting an end to sexual harassment on public transport.
🚎
in addition to staff training, which already began this week, an e-learning platform (www.teampueak.org) was launched for bor kor sor employees and those in other transport companies to educate themselves on the subject. the website also provides free tools and guidance for members of the public when accessing as #teampueak (#teambuttin).
👨🏻‍✈️👩🏾‍✈️
the safe cities for women network consists of actionaid thailand, women’s wellbeing and gender and sexual justice program, thai health program, women and men progressive movement foundation and the four slum region network.

#stopsexualharassment #actionaid #ทีมเผือก #เมืองปลอดภัยเพื่อผู้หญิง #metoo #timesup

text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robe mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
จากที่ซินดี้ได้เริ่มทำ #donttellhowtodress ไม่มีวันไหนที่ซินดี้รู้สึกเหนื่อย และการได้รับโล่ประกาศเกียรติ รางวัลบุคคลที่มีชื่อเสียงที่ไม่นิ่งเฉยต่อความรุนแรงในครอบครัวสตรีและเด็ก จาก พลเอก ฉัตรชัย สาริกัลยะ รองนายกรัฐมนตรีในวันนี้ทำให้ซินดี้มีกำลังใจที่จะทำตรงนี้ต่อไป ❤️🇹🇭🏆 #grateful #advocacyaward #genderbasedviolence #womensrights #metoo #timesup #heforshe #unite @donttellmehowtodress 
so proud and grateful to be receiving an advocacy award for activism against gender-based violence from the deputy prime minister of thailand this morning. my #donttellmehowtodress campaign has gone from a spur-of-the-moment rant on social media to now a full-fledged campaign against victim blaming and rape culture in thailand and across the asia-pacific region. thank you to everyone who has supported me and this cause along the way. together we will help shape a safe and more respectful future for our children. onwards we march!

text:
<東京取材>﻿
﻿
毎日新聞社が主催する、「毎日ファッション大賞」が今年も行われました。﻿
これは、”ファッション”という、文化や産業に貢献された方への表彰式。﻿
﻿
新人賞 ・ 資生堂奨励賞には、「akikoaoki」 ( @akikoaoki_official )デザイナーの青木 明子氏。﻿
鯨岡阿美子賞には、資生堂企業文化紙”花椿”のアートディレクターを40年以上務める、仲條 正義氏。﻿
話題賞には皆様ご存知「ゾゾスーツ」、﻿
そして大賞は、「toga」( @togaarchives )の古田泰子氏が二度目の受賞！﻿
﻿
togaの古田氏は初めての大賞を受賞した2009年にも﻿
「トーガの洋服を着てほしいのは普通のol、人生の多くを過ごす職場に、好きなものを着て行ってほしい」と語っており、﻿
#metoo などワードが飛び交った今年、あらためて二度目の大賞を受賞。変わらぬ芯の強い概念でパワーを与え続けて欲しいです❣️❣️❤︎﻿
﻿
﻿
表彰式の後は「akikoaoki 」の19ssのショーも披露されました！﻿
﻿
両ブランドから共通して感じるのは、﻿
環境に惑わされずきちんと自我を主張できる芯の強い人間像。﻿
ファッションの力ってこれこれ！と﻿
心の底から大きな拍手。おめでとうございます！﻿
﻿
#毎日ファッション大賞 #mfgrandprix﻿
@mainichi_fashion_grand_prix

text:
i’m not going to lie. this thanksgiving felt harder than last years and i’m unsure why. perhaps it’s because my whole self was preoccupied with taking care of a newborn and this year were more settled into the routine of a one year old. but remembering the details of my past, the thanksgiving 28 years ago that stole something precious from me...it’s been hard. today was hard. 
i felt like i was doing it wrong. not being able to separate the feelings of my questions and the hurt that it’s caused through so many years and feeling thankful at how far i’ve come and where i am today. 
i am thankful though. this man has not only unconditionally shown me for 16 years what a healthy love looks like, but he also gives me permission to feel in whatever way helps me the most. today, that meant that i cried in his arms and asked for answers to questions we didn’t have the answers for. that meant he held me. he told me how proud he was of me. he promised to take care of me and our kids. he invited me to share my grief and he grieved with me during it all. but mostly, he loved me. broken, tarnished, messy me. unconditionally. 
and i’m reminded that he loves me this much, how much greater does god love me?! bad things happen to people. we live in a fallen world where free will makes awful choices and leaves behind devastating consequences. but god is greater and he works through pain to bring about change to accomplish his will. 
today’s pain reminded me of his great mercy and compassion and how much he loves me. he brought a noble, godly man into my life who shows me daily what real love and respect for women looks like. 
i’m thankful for so many things, but today, especially today, i’m thankful for that! (if you’re unsure of what i’m talking about, you can watch my “always more” highlight in my feed. it explains a lot). ______
#marriage #stayingido #metoo #thanksgiving #husbandandwife #faithful #unconditionallove

text:
låt oss aldrig gå tillbaka igen. aldrig mer tillbaka till tystnadskulturen. skammen hör hemma hos förövaren. machokulturen måste bort, en ny manlighet införas. samtycke är lag. 
det finns mycket kvar att göra såklart och det börjar med dig och mig. låt oss ta ett steg framåt och fortsätta kämpa för en värld fri från sexuellt våld. ▫️
👀 syntolkning:
● utrikes 2018 har varit ett tufft år för världen: fler terror- och hatbrott har skett, klimatförändringarna blir värre och så har vi den humanitära katastrofen i jemen. men det finns flera saker att vara tacksamma över, skriver washington posts amanda erickson i en analys och listar sju saker.  erickson lyfter bland annat införandet av dataskyddsförordningen gdpr, etiopien och eritrea har slutit fred och de 13 thailändska pojkarna som var fast i en grotta räddades.  hon belyser även att me too-rörelsen spreds och blev ett globalt upprop. ”hur olika samhällen – några liberala, andra konservativa – såg på sexuella trakasserier ser ut att börja förändras”, skriver hon.
källa: @omni.se #metoo #metoosweden

text:
a cupcake won’t stop men’s violence against women but it can start a conversation. 
white ribbon day highlights the need to end men's violence against women.

it encourages the amazing, beautiful good men of this world to stand up and commit to never excusing or remaining silent about violence against women.

women alone can not end the violence because the men who commit violence against women don't respect us so we need the great men of this world to stand up beside us and, to speak out and act to help create the change needed to end men's violence against women.

last weekend basically spent 48 hours in these rooms. can we realize how weird it is that 2/3 women are worried about sexual harassment when they go to music festivals and that 23% have avoided going out due to risk of sexual assault. ⠀
⠀
nowwhat is a hackathon, where individuals meet to come up with concrete and innovative solutions for the prevention of sexual harassment and abuse in our society. the nightlife should be a space where everyone is respected and able to have fun. still, having to put up with different kinds of harassment is a part of the clubbing culture. usually it’s the victims of harassment that leave the club rather than the harasser.  there is a need to change people’s behaviour while clubbing.⠀
⠀
⠀
looking forward to a less intense weekend than the last one :) ⠀
⠀
⠀

text:
a face to the organisation. this is me, lisa. 💜
i’m a woman, who, was broken, damaged, down on the floor. a woman who fought with everything she had inside her, to find the tools, that would give her back her self-esteem, her self-worth. a woman, who truly understands the inner demons and battles a fellow survivor faces just to get out of bed in the morning.
💜
i’m a survivor. i’m a warrior. i haven’t always been. i’ve been broken. i was broken. i fought hard. i had to fight hard. i refused to be the victim. i didn’t want to be a victim. i wanted to survive. somewhere, somehow, i found hope. deep within, i found hope. hope for a better future, hope that i would still make it. hope i would still find my prince charming. i kept fighting, i kept surviving, then, i did it, i found my hope.

text:
i think soloway wrote/published this book too soon. 
jill soloway is the show runner for transparent, who came out as non-binary not too long ago and who, ironically, was seen as a leader in the #metoo movement even though later transparent’s star jeffrey tambor was accused of sexually harassing two trans employees on the set of the show. 
in this title, we get a little hollywood gossip, some insider stuff about how tv works these days, and the deeply selfish and fascinating story of how a person traversed their midlife and identity crises. 
i say “too soon” because i feel like soloway is still in the midst of everything: reckoning with an abuser on their show, reckoning with their gender identity, and wrestling with self awareness in general and how their decisions and behaviors impact the people in their lives. 
one twitter person wondered if soloway gave all non-binary people a bad name with their selfishness, self absorption and outrageous privilege. 
i think they are honestly wrestling with these things (in addition to wanting to topple the patriarchy). a few more years of self work probably would have made for a better, more reflective memoir. despite its unfinished feeling, i still appreciated its attempts at sharing soloway’s growing understanding of the dynamic changes occurring within queer and feminist culture. #bookstagram #nonfiction #feminism #queerculture #shewantsitbook
name: Jen "Book obsessed" F-A

text:
1️⃣2️⃣. #gaslighting.
.
.
. 
the #metoo uproar has spread like a wildfire. it gave courage to a lot of people irrespective of the gender, to speak up. but for a few individuals like me, it was a dark realisation. for people who've been victims of gaslighting and emotional abuse, it wasn't about sharing with the world. rather it was a very bleak space they went in again, reliving all the details and gory memories. i could sense all the anxiety building up again. sleepless nights and bunch of nightmares waiting to haunt me the moment i closed my eyes. it was only after 5 years of having gone through psychological abuse that i realised i was in a relationship with a gaslighter. was i at fault ? nope. people like me are easy to manipulate. especially if you're sensitive and naive, the world doesn't get any easy. right now, i'm in a better space. i'm much more aware of myself and the surroundings. let me be very specific this isn't a cry for pity or help. it's just about how we treat ourselves and trust the people we love blindly. our generation wants instant gratification. we don't want to wait. we want it all and we're willing to do it all for people we're in love with. are you sure they love you back ? are you even sure its love ? it's always good to check on yourself. we're not taught self love or self care but it's never too late. to people who lived through all of this alone, without sharing it with the world, kudos. i hope you get the courage to step out of an emotionally abusive relationship (if you are in one). at first, it may be difficult to even recognise this. i hope and pray you get signs or something to help you step out of this. it's okay to let go. to those who think a good partner doesn't exist, give it some time. it's all about loving yourself first. for real. not to make it all philosophical. we all deserve to be happy. don't let the world change you. you're the best you. ❤️ #loveandlight

text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
i am becoming a free person. i realized we are all made of strength and struggle as my wife @mrsjazminemarie has told me time and time again. 
the next episode of “the fresh life” will explore the areas of being a “man” in ways many of you at have never heard. men are being crushed under the weight of perfectionism and being soldiers of strength by the millions. what you see as a powerful masculine man, is really a powerless masculine man hoping you don’t see what’s behind his sword and shield. because if you had a chance to get a glimpse of what’s behind mine, you would see pain, suicidal wishes, uncertainty and lack of confidence in my past, and performing for approval. we are not our struggles but they are a beautiful portion of our life. 
episode 3... coming soon.
#thefreshlife #marriage #masculinity #donaldtrump #metoo #men #mentalhealth #quotes

text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin

text:
questa è più o meno la faccia che ho fatto quando ieri @debora.dusina mi ha segnalato un pezzo su “il post”, tradotto dal new york times che parlava di “nanoinfluencer”. copio e incollo un pezzetto per iniziare: “ai nanoinfluencer, invece, spesso può bastare ricevere un prodotto in omaggio, senza pagare, in cambio di un post sponsorizzato. […] rendono molto meno dei personaggi famosi, certo; ma costano anche molto meno. […] i nanoinfluencer non hanno grandi pretese, e in cambio di prodotti gratis o piccoli compensi dicono qualsiasi cosa le aziende vogliano”. boia, mi trasmetti una credibilità così che ciao. poi sarebbero da una parte più credibili perché non smarchetterebbero a destra e a manca come fanno invece i colleghi micro e big influencer (cito un altro pezzetto: “ma anche per questo hanno un rapporto spontaneo e non artificioso con i propri followers”), però poi sarebbero disposti a tutto e a fare da marionetta dell’azienda pur di scroccare prodotti, e parlarne bene nonostante, magari, facciano cagare. il punto qui sta a priori. non tanto nei nanoinfluencer che funzionerebbero alla grande, essendo spontanei da una parte e dall’altra smarchettando la qualsiasi (!), ma sulla qualità della comunicazione. poi sinceramente? non la vedo tanto lontana da una che si prostituisce pur di fare un film. anzi.
#metoo lavoro per la gloria (suka). ho scritto un blogpost lunghissimo a proposito. vi metto il link in bio e nelle stories, leggetelo se potete, dato che parlo anche di #advsensate, l’utopia di una svolta modalità “carosello digitale” e di gruppi telegram per scambio commenti. 📷 @mauroserra_portraits

text:
【關於公投】

大家好，今天要說一個性侵伴隨霸凌的故事。

不，欣儀是意境，主角是我。

國中二年級正值情竇初開，但又懵懵懂懂，學校沒有教，所以就跟著同學一起摸黑尋找，有樣學樣去戀愛。他，是我人生第一個稱為男朋友的人，但現在回想也不過是以愛為名的侵犯。

他不斷向我提出性需求，我都似懂非懂的帶過，持續到第13天，那天一群人到他家作客，其他朋友先走，而他再度對我提出性要求，但這次不同，他恐嚇若不同意就分手。我害怕極了，對一個沒想法與經驗的國中生來說，聽到這句話時全世界都在崩塌邊緣，當時的我不知道這樣是不尊重我身體自主權的要求，也不知道這種權力不對等的情況稱為性侵，我甚至連我可以主張什麼都不知道，事情就這麼發生了。

在沒有正確性觀念的情況，加上生理本身不夠成熟下，他嘗試進入就已經讓我瘋狂顫抖，疼痛盤據、鮮血直流，且無人留心是否擦拭，他對待我的方式，就像我是個沒生命的軀殼一樣。突然，他阿嬤上來敲門，我一點尊嚴也沒有得裸身躲藏在陽台。當然後來也沒繼續，他怕被發現所以用最快的速度將我偷渡出家門，像垃圾一樣將我丟在路旁。我自己走路回家，被掏空的身體緩步前行。
我覺得這一切太可怕，但卻不知道為什麼會有這種感覺。當晚我沒跟任何人提起，確實感到難受但又不知道如何啟齒。
#性無知最可怕的地方在於，#連自己受傷了都不知道。

隔天他消失了，我的世界正式崩塌。
我在教室放聲大哭，抽抽噎噎道出自己的遭遇。誰知道換來的不是同學的關切，而是傳得整間學校沸沸揚揚，我被閒話、被恥笑，多難聽的話我都直接或間接聽過，待在教室會有人刻意前來看我長怎樣，走在走廊上會聽到有人罵我髒，甚至不熟的朋友會以輕佻的語調大喊說我是被幹過的，直到上大學還能聽到有人在捏造不實內容妖魔化我。

那時候，有好多我不懂的事。
為什麼我受傷了，每個人都對著我訕笑？ 
為什麼明明與我有同樣遭遇的人，也要跟著欺負我？
為什麼錯的不是我，但大家對我的態度像在懲罰我？
為什麼我都已經痛得無法言語，卻無從獲得任何溫暖？
受害者被檢討的過程，我經歷過千千萬萬次。

滿是疑惑，然遍尋不著解答，所以我選擇逃。
求學過程不斷往沒有人認識我的地方去，但這種閒話的附著力通常很強，每矢口否認一次，就是在那個早已傷痕纍纍的自己身上再劃上一刀。
逃跑過程中也學會武裝。國中時活成小太妹，膨脹自己才沒有人敢再欺負我。高中表面上過得充實，其實盡是焦慮，每每上台，總覺得台下的細語是在非議我。然後才明白，過不了自己那關，逃到哪都是枉然。
直到上大學，接觸女性主義、性別議題與理論，我才發現自己並不是異類，從中挖掘自我認同的根基，才漸漸從逃避與武裝中解脫。

我喜歡窩在圖書館一整天，將自己浸淫在文字裡頭，從中長出自己該有的模樣，才敢回頭審視這一段不堪。
然後發現沒有人願意是壞人，魯莽嘗試又驚慌出逃的他，獵奇探看且輕蔑調侃的同學，都是因為不知道。
沒有正確尋求資訊的管道，只能以戲弄的方式靠近。
女性主義教會我放下仇恨，當個溫柔而堅強的女人。
我也不再怪罪傷害我的人，這從來就是結構性問題。

但如果當時能夠有完善的教育、充分的資訊，甚至一位觀念開放的良師益友，真真切切地望入我的雙眼告訴我：#你沒有錯、#是他的錯、#是社會的錯，或許傷口痊癒會快得多。

德國性教育早在小一就開始，香港也是將性教育課程完善分成認識身體、性行為、避孕方式，並帶出愛、承擔與責任，相比之下臺灣現行教育僅帶出生理構造與男女差異，粗糙而暴力。

參照葉永鋕的例子，我們知道及早行使性平教育的重要，因為你不會知道你的孩子的性別氣質是否為「主流」，是否出生就面對一連串的壓迫與定型。同樣，及早性教育也很重要，因為你不知道你的孩子是否會因無知而受害、加害，甚至已經受傷卻渾然不知。

#及早接受性教育真的很重要。
建構正確觀念、畫好身心靈界線後，才會明白哪些可以接受、哪些必須拒絕，也才知道怎麼尊重所有人的身體自主權。
除了了解自己的權益，懂得保護自己、懂得怎麼求救外，也更不會無意間成為加害者，粗暴得創造出一次次二度傷害。

你問我痊癒了嗎？雖然撰寫這一切時，仍本能性地逃避事發經過，自揭瘡疤真的不好受，但時空流轉，它已然成為我身體的一部分，催促我站出來說些什麼，可能是#你沒有錯，可能是#metoo。

最後謝謝自己的勇敢。
明天就要投票了呢，一起寫下歷史吧！

#20181124
#公投第15案我蓋同意
#性教育永遠都不嫌早
#taiwan#tainan#longci#portrait#photography#portraitphotography#visualsoflife#portraitmood#portrait_shot#iseetaiwan#amazingtaiwan#discovertaiwan#exploretaiwan#vscotaiwan#bpintaiwan

我喜歡窩在圖書館一整天，將自己浸淫在文字裡頭，從中長出自己該有的模樣，才敢回頭審視這一段不堪。
然後發現沒有人願意是壞人，魯莽嘗試又驚慌出逃的他，獵奇探看且輕蔑調侃的同學，都是因為不知道。
沒有正確尋求資訊的管道，只能以戲弄的方式靠近。
女性主義教會我放下仇恨，當個溫柔而堅強的女人。
我也不再怪罪傷害我的人，這從來就是結構性問題。

但如果當時能夠有完善的教育、充分的資訊，甚至一位觀念開放的良師益友，真真切切地望入我的雙眼告訴我：沒有錯、他的錯、社會的錯，或許傷口痊癒會快得多。

德國性教育早在小一就開始，香港也是將性教育課程完善分成認識身體、性行為、避孕方式，並帶出愛、承擔與責任，相比之下臺灣現行教育僅帶出生理構造與男女差異，粗糙而暴力。

參照葉永鋕的例子，我們知道及早行使性平教育的重要，因為你不會知道你的孩子的性別氣質是否為「主流」，是否出生就面對一連串的壓迫與定型。同樣，及早性教育也很重要，因為你不知道你的孩子是否會因無知而受害、加害，甚至已經受傷卻渾然不知。

早接受性教育真的很重要。
建構正確觀念、畫好身心靈界線後，才會明白哪些可以接受、哪些必須拒絕，也才知道怎麼尊重所有人的身體自主權。
除了了解自己的權益，懂得保護自己、懂得怎麼求救外，也更不會無意間成為加害者，粗暴得創造出一次次二度傷害。

你問我痊癒了嗎？雖然撰寫這一切時，仍本能性地逃避事發經過，自揭瘡疤真的不好受，但時空流轉，它已然成為我身體的一部分，催促我站出來說些什麼，可能是沒有錯，可能是etoo。

最後謝謝自己的勇敢。
明天就要投票了呢，一起寫下歷史吧！

教育永遠都不嫌早

text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
нобелевскую премию, конечно, штормит в этом году и даже они не остались в стороне от такого популярного метода привлечения внимания, как #скандал. .
.
но обо все по порядку. самой модной темой 2018г был #харрасмент (домогательство — причиняющее неудобство или вред поведение, нарушающее неприкосновенность частной жизни лица). но приемлемой книги о харрасменте так и не нашлось.

text:
i needed a reminder of how far i've come in my recovery. 
my ex from jail who's out of jail messaged me tonight. 
my first immediate thought? panic 
i was kinda numb but i couldnt stop shaking

then? 
feelings 
so. many. feelings.

i'm very grateful for having a support system. i let one of the people know and i just typed out how i felt in that moment. it was long and back and forth.. but it wasn't a bottle or a razor. or anything else to harm myself. 
i still have to work out these feelings but i could feel the relapse vibes bubbling. so i continued watching youtube and editing a video and just living my life. 
he can not stop me from living my life. not again. 
so tomorrow i'll deal with the feelings or today since its 3am (forgot my sleeping gummy) 
but for now i need to rest. i need to breathe. 
i am safe. 
i am 6 months sober and almost 1 year from self harm. i am going to school again. i am working on myself. i'm not distracted in a relationship. 
i got this. 🍓 
i'm also not alone. others go through what i have too and it sucks and it's unfair and its cruel. but were warriors. 
we got this

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

tweet_full:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin

text:
sinds het losbarsten van #metoo is er (gelukkig!) meer aandacht van werkgevers voor seksueel grensoverschrijdend gedrag op de werkvloer. van hogescholen en universiteiten horen we nog weinig. en dat terwijl studentes statistisch gezien de meeste kans lopen om slachtoffer te worden. 
am community lid @tesseltenzweege moest tijdens haar uitwisseling aan de san francisco state university een verplicht online vak volgen over grensoverschrijdend gedrag. ze vroeg zich daardoor af hoe het eigenlijk zit met de voorlichting en preventie op haar eigen onderwijsinstelling @uva_amsterdam. ze ging op onderzoek uit en schreef hierover op @pisswife; het platform dat ze samen met @helenweeres oprichtte. je vindt de link naar het artikel op onze fb pagina! 📸 @ib_vision #blog #knowledgeispower #ambitieuzemeisjes #feminist #womensupportingwomen #safetyfirst #shoutout #activist

text: here is the reason why i posted the #metoo poll earlier this week. this aristocats jumbo, although it is not very expensive, was dangled in front of my face when i was barely 18 by a man in his mid 30s and was told the only thing he’d trade it for was a kiss from me. at first i thought “well, its just a kiss.” but then my morals reminded me that my body and my integrity, not just as a pin trader but also as a human being, was worth so much more than an $80 piece of metal. last week i bought it on ebay for half that price, and i couldnt be more proud of myself to stick by my morals. people from all corners of the earth will push you by any means they can think of, but if you stick by your morals, it will feel so much more rewarding. be a first place trophy, not a doorknob💁🏻‍♀️ 👌🏻aristocats nft/nfs, incredibles jumbo is spoken for👌🏻

text:
jetzt im handel: das büchermagazin 01/2019 mit unserem jährlichen kinderliteratur-sonderheft kinderbücher. und das sind unsere themen:

literarische zeitreisen: dörte hansen („altes land“) hat mit uns über brinkebüll gesprochen, das fiktive dorf aus ihrem neuen roman „mittagsstunde“. peter pranges roman „eine familie in deutschland“ erzählt von den jahren vor dem kriegsbeginn 1939. in unserem titelinterview spricht er nicht nur über die nazizeit, sondern auch über das erstarken der nationalen populisten in der gegenwart. bis ins jahr 1820 führt karen duves neuer roman „fräulein nettes kurzer sommer“, der die romantik ironisch entlarvt.

feministisch lesen: @zeilenkino stellt großartige sachbücher und romane vor, die ein jahr nach der #metoo-debatte position zu feministischen fragestellungen beziehen.

im leseart-spezial: 114 bibliophile geschenkideen. sinnlich, genussvoll und eigensinnig – unsere lieblingsbücher 2018.

ausserdem: till raethers aktueller krimi „unter wasser“ dreht sich um die entführung einer bekannten youtuberin in einem spaßbad. meike dannenberg unterhielt sich mit dem autor über moderne mediennutzung und deren schattenseiten. der anthropologe und aktivist david graeber erklärt in seinem buch „bullshit-jobs“, was es mit menschen macht, wenn sie ihre arbeit als sinnlos empfinden. pernille fischer christensen hat einen berührenden film über die jugendjahre astrid lindgrens gedreht. und der ehemalige @greenpeace.de-chef und @foodwatch_de-gründer thilo bode spricht über sein neues buch „die dikatur der konzerne“, das von christian brückner wunderbar als hörbuch umgesetzt wird.

mit gastbeiträgen von @haukeharder (leseschatz) und hannah welte (@queerbuch). erhältlich im gut sortierten zeitschriftenhandel, in vielen buchhandlungen und online: https://www.falkemedia-shop.de/hobby/buecher-magazin/buecher-01/2019

text:
задумывая о прикорме малыша, немаловажно подумать о покупке посуды для ребёнка🐣

у ребёнка должна быть индивидуальная посуда:
✅личная гигиена;
✅личное пространство.
❗️посуда должна быть безопасна - не разбиваться при падении, и не быть токсичной. 😍важен критерий эргономичности, а также тактильные и визуальные свойства посуды. 
наша посуда из бамбука, 💯% соответствует заданным требованиям и подходит для малышей от 6 месяцев до 6 лет, ✔️ею можно пользоваться достаточно долго, при правильной эксплуатации. ❗️и помните - здоровьем ребёнка нельзя рисковать! выбирая нашу посуду вы делаете шаг здоровому образу жизни!

text:
”black friday” was originally the day of a suffragette demonstration i london, november 18th 1910 where many feminists were violated and abused by authorities for wanting the right to vote. picture number 2 is sojourner truth, suffraget in the us during the 19th century. she fought for the right of black women to vote, something that was ignored by some suffragettes back then. nowdays all feminists will stand united- thats our mission- weather in saudi, somalia, the us, china or sweden where i am from. ❤️ think about the women who suffered for the freedom of women in the west- now lets fight together with the women in the east). سمي يوم الجمعة الأسود بعد مظاهرة لحق المرأة في التصويت في لندن عام ١٩١٠ عندما قامت السلطات بالاعتداء والمعاملة السيئة للنسويات بسبب رغبتهن في امتلاك حقهن بالتصويت. الصورة رقم 2 هي سوجورنر تروث ، ناشطة في حقوق المرأة في الولايات المتحدة خلال القرن التاسع عشر. كافحت من أجل حق النساء السود في التصويت ، وهو أمر تجاهلته بعض المطالبات لحق المرأة في التصويت البيض في ذلك الوقت. واليوم ، ستقف جميع النسويات متحدين. هذه طبيعة مهمتنا في السعودية أو الصومال أو الولايات المتحدة أو الصين أو السويد التي انتمي إليها. ❤️ يوم سعيد لأناس الجمعة السوداء (فكروا في النساء اللواتي عانين من أجل حرية المرأة في الغرب ، والآن لنحارب سويا مع النساء في الشرق).
#blackfriday #suffragettes #feminism #feminist #blm #blacklivesmatter #solidarity #sistership #sisterhood #metoo #timesup #stopenslavingsaudiwomen #saudiwomen #london #uk #saudiarabia

text: partant du constat qu’aucune mobilisation de terrain d’ampleur n’avait vu le jour en france à la suite des mouvements #metoo ou #balancetonporc, un collectif d’associations féministes, de citoyennes et de personnalités ont décidé d’organiser, une « déferlante féministe contre les violences sexistes et sexuelles ». a l’image de ce qui a pu se passer en espagne, en argentine ou encore au chili, les membres du collectif #noustoutes espèrent voir des milliers de femmes défiler dans les rues le samedi 24 novembre prochain.

l’ombra del meu amor sense casa.
la bala que travessa l’ombra del meu amor sense casa.

els meus ulls que arrelen en el vent que arrenca les fulles
que cobreixen la bala que travessa l’ombra del meu amor sense casa.
el meu amor que s’emmiralla en els ulls que arrelen en el vent
que arrenca les fulles que cobreixen la bala que travessa l’ombra
del meu amor sense casa.
maria-mercè marçal, «el meu amor sense casa».
.

text: today is #whiteribbonday — this is some of my story: it was in the seedy hours of the morning, before the sun had even risen, that i was drugged, held down and raped. i woke up a few hours later—bloody, sore and wedged between two men. one, i knew. (attacker #2) at the time we were sort of seeing each other. i liked him. the other— the best friend (attacker #1) whom i had only met that evening briefly and who i felt nothing for. he didn’t look like a face i should have feared and steered clear from. his smile was warm, he dressed well and he smelt of musky cologne. i think back to that night and i try to find warning signs in his behaviour. but i never find any. i blamed myself relentlessly for months. i was being sexually harassed by another guy at the party and attacker #1 appeared to be my ‘rescuer’ and ‘saved’ me from him, taking me to the bedroom and telling me to get some rest. he told me i’d be safe in there. he left and shut the door behind him. i must’ve fallen asleep as there is still a gap missing between that moment and the next however many minutes or hours the rape lasts. i have no concept of time. i have only fractions of moments, milliseconds of memories... like tiny little flashes from cameras. i remember telling my body to stop him, to push him off, but my body couldn’t. i felt, paralysed. trapped and unable to save myself, i closed my eyes and let sleep take my life that night. when i awoke, i was completely naked, and they were too. attacker #1 was still asleep, attacker #2 was awake. it must not have phased him that his best mate was on the other side of me, and that the remnants of blood and semen stained my skin. before i had even fully opened my eyes i could feel his fingers inside of me and he was kissing my back. i remember my entire body freezing and for some reason i was holding my breath. it hurt so much. it stung and i felt sick. i felt like i was unable to stop him too— like it was too late and he already owned the rights to my body. i didn’t say ‘no’, but my body and the circumstances did not say ‘yes’. when he was done, he turned over and fell straight back to sleep. within a minute he was snoring. #speakup #metoo

text:
i feel him coming closer to me,
i feel my heart racing and my hands feeling numb,
i feel anger and hatred.
i feel disgust and horror,
i feel his hands on my mouth trying to stop my screams for help from coming out,
i feel solitude because i can't tell anyone,
i feel anxious thinking about the next time it'll happen,
i feel the urge to cry and beg for help,
i feel feelings i would never want anyone to feel,
i feel helpless.

a six year old with hopeless eyes,
a seven year old with a little courage,
an eight year old trying to fight for her body,
a nine year old finally free from a demon which possessed her for years,
tortured her, bruised her and took away hope from her.
and finally a fifteen year old strong enough to put her trauma into words and make it sound beautiful.
#metoo

text:
ich bin immer wieder überrascht davon, wie deutlich patriarchale strukturen hervortreten können! wie z.b. gestern auf einem vortrag der abendveranstaltung des styrian strategy summit der karl-franzens-universität graz. chefstratege der abu dhabi national oil company, professor rose, der in seinen ausführungen den klimawandel auf das enorme weltbevölkerungswachstum zurückführte, lieferte auch gleich die passende lösung für das problem: mehr sexualerziehung für frauen! aufgrund vorangegangener aussagen gehe ich davon aus, dass damit vor allem frauen aus dem globalen süden gemeint sind. zugegeben, „mehr kondome“ (für alle? 🤔) war ein weiterer lösungsansatz des professors für entrepreneurship und angewandte bwl - aber letztlich liege die verantwortung fürs kinderkriegen ja doch immer noch bei den frauen. 
gegen ende des vortrags, der meiner meinung nach nicht mehr als den (kläglichen) versuch darstellte, das image von ölkonzernen aufzupolieren, wurde ich noch einmal hellhörig: so etwas wie sexismus gäbe es in der ölindustrie schon lange nicht mehr! wer sich einen sexistischen witz erlaube, wäre direkt weg vom fenster! #metoo ??? „so etwas gibt es bei uns nicht!“
sehr geehrter herr professor rose, 
in anlehnung an diese - meines erachtens - doch sehr fragwürdigen aussagen, lade ich sie herzlich dazu ein, ihren vortrag noch einmal kritisch zu reflektieren und möglicherweise vorhandene diskrepanzen zu korrigieren!
mit freundlichen grüßen 
frau frank
.
.
.
#oilcompany #styrianstrategysummit #kfugraz #entrepreneurship #bwl #intersectionalfeminism #sexism #sexismus #intersektionalität #patriarchy #patriarchalsociety #patriarchatskritik #metoo #feministfriday #feministfriends #university #genderstudies #fraufrank_

text:
islandia es a menudo considerada como un ejemplo de la igualdad de género. pero la primera ministra, katrin jakobsdottir, dijo a dw que incluso su país tiene que seguir trabajando. 
katrin jakobsdottir: muchas veces he dicho que, a pesar de que estamos orgullosos del puesto que ocupamos en el "world economic forum´s global gender gap”, las mujeres en islandia también somos consientes de que tenemos que seguir trabajando. si bien hay una diferencia entre la igualdad de género en islandia y en otros rincones del mundo, la naturaleza de la discriminación es la misma. la brecha salarial todavía existe, las mujeres no tienen el mismo poder en el mundo empresarial y financiero del país, y también tenemos graves problemas de violencia de género, acoso, y violencia sexual. muchos casos fueron revelados luego del movimiento #metoo.

text:
blaming the victim...
one reason people blame a victim is to distance themselves from an unpleasant occurrence and thereby confirm their own invulnerability to the risk. by labeling or accusing the victim, others can see the victim as different from themselves. people reassure themselves by thinking, "because i am not like her, because i do not do that, this would never happen to me." we need to help people understand that this is not a helpful reaction. victim-blaming attitudes marginalize the victim/survivor and make it harder to come forward and report the abuse. if the survivor knows that you or society blames her for the abuse, s/he will not feel safe or comfortable coming forward and talking to you. victim-blaming attitudes also reinforce what the abuser has been saying all along; that it is the victim’s fault this is happening. it is not the victim’s fault or responsibility to fix the situation; it is the abuser’s choice. by engaging in victim-blaming attitudes, society allows the abuser to perpetrate relationship abuse or sexual assault while avoiding accountability for his/her actions. #rape #blamethevictim #abuse #metoo #funny #dankmemes #feminism #dank #sexualabuse #fortnite #sexualassault #rapevictim #rapeculture #feminist #love #anime #women #sex #lmao #domesticviolence #woman #autism #survivor #nomore #victim #blaming #whyididntreport.

elsewhere in the country, the majority of girls and women are cut. now, sudan's government, with help from international aid, is hoping to put an end to fgm nationwide, by 2030.

it comes as the british government announces £50m to tackle the issue across the continent. the bbc's senior africa correspondent anne soy went to meet some of the people turning their back on the practice and witnessed the change they are bringing to their communities.

text:
time with family 🙏 people who make me laugh 🙏 waking up to a bright blue sky 🙏 @iamadamtau 🙏 friends who’ve stuck by me for 30+ years 🙏 friends who’ve stuck by me for 20+ years 🙏 friends i’m starting to get close with 🙏 friends i’ve only just met 🙏 being able to dance 🙏 instructing at @305fitness 🙏 perfectly burnt brussels 🙏 greece 🙏 it’s showtime on the subway 🙏 gyms that have all the best equipment and are clean 🙏 power suits 🙏 parents calling just to say hi at random times 🙏 clients allowing and trusting me to push them out of their comfort zone 🙏 the look in someone’s eye when you’ve inspired them to do big things 🙏 brooklyn 🙏 thanksgiving parade 🙏 harry hugs 🙏 getting paid 🙏 memories that make you smile 🙏 memories that make you laugh 🙏 memories that make you stronger 🙏 30+ years of good health 🙏🙏 wendy williams 🙏 #metoo 🙏 royalties 🙏 ever changing nyc 🙏 trader joe’s 🙏 disneyworld 🙏 being able to travel 🙏 feeling safe 🙏 the first spring leaves 🙏 sharing in my friends’ happinesses, blessings & joys 🙏 oceans 🙏 broccoli 🙏 traditions 🙏 having a home that feels like home 🙏 bursts of inspiration 🙏 the strength to stand up for myself in challenging moments 🙏 bravo tv 🙏 netflix 🙏 the internet 🙏 seriously good rosé 🙏 my failures 🙏 hearing beautiful voices you actually feel in your gut 🙏 living in a country in which i can own and grow a business 🙏 fancy mac & cheese once in awhile 🙏 when the subway shows up right away 🙏 when all the lights are green 🙏 inside jokes 🙏 dishwashers and washing machines 🙏 feeling a part of something bigger 🙏 creative minds who change our world 🙏 espresso 🙏 the rare commercials that actually make you laugh 🙏 new york magazine 🙏 a fresh pair of sneakers 🙏 being “in the zone” 🙏 knowing i could write a list of all the things i feel grateful for and never run out. that truly is the most special of all. 
#thanksigiving #gratitudeistheattitude #graditudelist

taking over @opensocietyfoundations ’s instagram for a week with photos from the argentina's chapter of 'ni una menos'.
glad to have opportunity to give visibility on this important and current issue in the week of november 25th, the international day for the elimination of violence against women.
thanks a lot to maggie soladay.

www.niunamenosproject.com
@karlitomancini
@ribovale
@irupetentorio 
@rijeka30 
#repost @opensocietyfoundations
(@get_repost)
• • •
a woman and her three daughters. after dozens of appeals to the police went unanswered, this woman separated from her abusive ex-husband. still, she cannot count on local law enforcement to protect her rights. 
despite a 2012 law which raised the maximum prison sentence for “femicide,” the killing of a woman or girl on account of her gender, argentina is still struggling against widespread gender-based violence. thankfully, a grassroots, women-led movement known as ni una menos (not one [woman] less) has arisen in argentina, and is working to empower women and defend their human rights. in this series, karl mancini (@karlitomancini) shares some of his work on the inspiring women of ni una menos and their fight for justice. to learn more about both mancini's work and ni una menos, please follow the link in our bio.

text:
i’m working towards being more open with everyone about my struggles.
i had a lot of interesting and unexpected feedback from my last post; friends and loved ones checking in, making sure i was doing okay.
•
this told me two things.
•
one: i have an amazing support system who care about my success.
•
and two: i’m not as open about my personal struggles as i thought.
•
so a brief update for those who care: i suffered severe birth trauma when birthing jb. i denied the inconvenient mental burden that physical trauma invites along. add too this cracked plate the mental burden of having a sick child who defies medical norms plus the day to day grind of parenting a 2 and a 3 year old and the stress mounted.
i have since been diagnosed with general anxiety disorder and have taken steps towards processing and accepting my reality.
•
anxiety makes me short tempered. anxiety makes me impatient. anxiety makes me irritable, lazy and mean (mostly to myself). anxiety makes me feel like i am not enough.
•
i am not those things. i am more than my anxiety. anxiety is real, it is strong, but it isn’t my whole story.
i am also a mother, a nurturer, an educator, and a healer. my children make me whole and remind me what is important.
•
it is with in mind that i have begun a journey of self reflection and personal healing. it won’t be easy, nothing meaningful ever is. but we all have so much to gain. so here goes nothing.
•

text:
in 1973, india launched its programme “project tiger” and tiger was made the national animal of india. similar approach to save many endangered species was seen and is still can be seen in various parts of india, be it in the case of rhinos or lions. but why don’t we ever question the animals for being killed, is it not amusing that the rhinos or blackbucks are never pointed fingers at for tempting the poachers? or is my amusement ridiculously stupid? i’ll assume you’re smart enough to go for the latter.

why then are the sexually abused blamed rather than the abuser? the clothes that tempt, the alcohol and friendly behavior that give away hints of “come rape me”. why did people find it normal back then and unfortunately even now? “to rape” is a crime, not to “be raped”. deep rooted is the idea “men is superior” and no matter how much we come with historical examples of “women empowerment”, it never changes the truth that our entire history was sexist. we “empower” women only because we weakened them at the first place, we continue to do so.

the society changes and the change is as important as air! but the change is so slow that generations pass away without justice. the elected representatives, college authorities, religious leaders, police and everyone who had to answer, answered the most illogically, and this is alarming.

if we cannot ensure justice and stay mum against the visible oppression then do we even have dignity?

#science #society #smashthepatriarchy #patriarchy
#victimblaming #victim  #metoo
#equality #instagram #respect #culture

text:
kom ihåg black friday! 
ja, alltså inte den som vill att du ska köpa så mycket som möjligt, utan den från 1910, då 300 suffragetter samlades utanför westminsterpalatset i london för att demonstrera för kvinnlig rösträtt. dagen blev känd som "black friday" för att de manliga poliserna, och de manliga åskådarna, mötte de kvinnliga demonstranterna med våld. delar av våldet var sexualiserat – bland annat vred polisen om flera demonstranters bröst, och en del våldshandlingar åtföljdes av vidriga, kränkande kommentarer.

några få generationer senare är året 2018 och vi förknippar "black friday" med köphets.

2018 har vi här i sverige äntligen fått en sexualbrottslagstiftning som definierar våldtäkt för vad det verkligen är; ofrivilligt sex, och som gör det möjligt att döma för våldtäkt även när gärningspersonen (som oftast är en man) saknar uppsåt. så många generationer av feminister står bakom den lagen, och vi hade aldrig kommit hit om det inte vore för våra historiska medsystrar, bland annat suffragetterna. 
och vi fortsätter!

just nu uppmärksammar vi de delar av vår politik som har starkast koppling till #metoo, bland annat vill vi: ♀ att åklagarmyndigheten och domstolsverket ges ökade resurser i syfte att kvalitetshöja rättsprocessen inom sexualbrott.
♀ se en skarp lagstiftning mot könsdiskriminerande reklam, en begränsning av porr och ett förbud mot strippklubbar, för att våra offentliga rum ska vara trygga för alla.
♀ att sverige genomför informationssatsningar kring samtycke och vad den nya lagen innebär.

och vi ska: ♀ verka för sexuella och reproduktiva rättigeter i eu enligt svensk modell, för våra medsyskons rätt till abort och samtyckeslagstiftning.

skriv under uppropet om du stöttar våra politiska förslag:
https://med.feministisktinitiativ.se/ga-langre-metoo

ska du köpa något idag, så köp ett medlemskap i f!
du är det viktigaste vi har. utan dig, inget f!

kom ihåg black friday! 
ja, alltså inte den som vill att du ska köpa så mycket som möjligt, utan den från 1910, då 300 suffragetter samlades utanför westminsterpalatset i london för att demonstrera för kvinnlig rösträtt. dagen blev känd som "black friday" för att de manliga poliserna, och de manliga åskådarna, mötte de kvinnliga demonstranterna med våld. delar av våldet var sexualiserat – bland annat vred polisen om flera demonstranters bröst, och en del våldshandlingar åtföljdes av vidriga, kränkande kommentarer.

några få generationer senare är året 2018 och vi förknippar "black friday" med köphets.

2018 har vi här i sverige äntligen fått en sexualbrottslagstiftning som definierar våldtäkt för vad det verkligen är; ofrivilligt sex, och som gör det möjligt att döma för våldtäkt även när gärningspersonen (som oftast är en man) saknar uppsåt. så många generationer av feminister står bakom den lagen, och vi hade aldrig kommit hit om det inte vore för våra historiska medsystrar, bland annat suffragetterna.

text: this is my daughter shelice. she’s 16 and truly amazing. she carries distinguished honors, takes ap classes, is a track star, a new driver, maintains a job, is considering several colleges and she recently finished atollo’s rigorous leadership program which was 6 weeks of 5-7am meetings (yes before school) where she gained the ability to complete the rubiks cube in less than 90 seconds among other wonderful things. words cannot express the awesomeness of this young lady, not just because she is my daughter, because she just is. when i was her age i was living on my own, working two jobs and going to school. i had experienced levels of pain and trauma that no one should ever have to endure, especially by the age of 16. i had no identity and just floated through this thing called life broken, unsure and lost. all i knew is i wanted something different for my life and the life of my children. to see her shine despite my fears that the world would hurt her as it did me, is indescribable. this, her, she...makes every ounce of healing worth it. if you have a daughter and are struggling in your own healing thinking you’re not worth it or that it will never happen for you, do it for her until you can do it for you ❤️. #restoringtheseed #soultherapy #healing #freedom #insight #trauma #metoo #love #selflove #daughter #light

text:
så stort att få va med! 😍 
i lördags, på årsdagen för samordningen av de bransch- och områdesspecifika metoouppropen, möttes vi igen. vi lyssnade på anna wahl och nina rung och klubbade också igenom en förening - en plattform för metoouppropen för att kunna jobba vidare för jämställdhet och lika villkor i arbetslivet 😀

här är lite foton från dagen. sorry för dålig bildkvalité på de sista, det var inte lätt att fota en skärm 🙏🏽 på de tre första, grym fotocred till gustav andersson lilliehorn, @gustav.film .
.
foto 1-3. 40 personer från 25 av uppropen på plats (65 upprop totalt)

4. 
time magazine utser person of the year 2017: silence breakers, alla kvinnor som brutit tystnaden kring sexuella trakasserier i usa. .
.
5. 
från gymnasieelevernas upprop.😖 .
. 
6. 
tidigare finansminister anders borg var förra året på fest. han visade där könet och kallade kvinnor för ”hora” och ”slampa”. försvar: han hade varit lite pressad sista tiden. själv har jag också varit sjukt pressad i perioder, för den sakens skull har jag dock aldrig känt mig tvungen att blotta mig och kalla män för könsord eller liknande. 🤔

7.
våldspyramiden är en modell som förenklat beskriver hur sexuellt våld skapas i vårt samhälle. googla den gärna 😊

8. nilla fischer håller ett bejublat tal på fotbollsgalan där hon adresserar kampen mot ojämlikhet och bjuder in männen att va med. hade varit fint om granen typ sagt: nu är vi med och förändrar! istället tycker han uttalandet är orättvist.
glöm inte: om ingen nämnt dig vid namn är du inte utpekad! va med och förändra istället för att bli defensiv. 😊

9. de flesta av oss är nog överens att vi vill se förändring. en bra start är att själv va den förändring du vill se. och killar, kom igen nu, ni tjänar också på jämställdhet så att ni äntligen får slippa leva i destruktiva roller som dikterar vad som anses manligt. män är överrepresenterade i olycksstatistiken, våldsstatistiken och självmordsstatistiken. se kopplingen mellan dessa fakta och en destruktiv mansroll som exempelvis säger att det är omanligt att prata om eller visa känslor, vara sårbar eller må dåligt. 
tillsammans framåt för förändring ❤️🙏🏽 #sanningenskagöraerfria #metoo

text:
‘tis the season to be jolly
…but should the suggestion of the christmas party be met with the same feeling and enthusiasm?
the inaugural festive do can be a daunting prospect for some employees, so should the expectation for everyone to attend exist? yes, the christmas party is your way of saying thank you, but your people have already dedicated 235 days, 1725 hours of their life to you this year, you can empathise that some may wish to pass on the bash. and indeed, for some employees with caring duties it may be an impossibility.
an invitation to the christmas party is key here – an invitation, rather than an expectation. for the most part, people will joyfully accept. but for those who don’t, they’ll appreciate your understanding and not being labelled a scrooge!  #gurls #workplace #woman #entrepreneur #femaleentrepreneur

text:
“jag har gått i feministiskt initiativs första maj-tåg mot ojämställdhet och ojämlikhet sedan 2015. vid något tillfälle under förra året bestämde jag mig för att jag ville göra något mer, något aktivt för kvinnokampen, och blev medlem i f!. jag är också aktivist i partiets ungdomsförbund, unga feminister.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
det största problemet är acceptansen för hur diskrimineringen mot kvinnor normaliseras samt hans sätt att vara mot henne, så att hon hamnar i ett underläge. det första steget är att bryta de mönster och strukturer som vårt samhälle är format utifrån. de innötta systemen gör att problemet inte bara kan suddas ut eller göras ogjorda, utan det krävs en utveckling. ett exempel på ett brytande av mönstret var hela #metoo rörelsen.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
det är viktigt att upprätthålla den kämpaglöd som så många kvinnor kände och fortfarande känner. kämpaglöden står för makten över henne själv, hennes kropp, sinne, åsikter och hur hon agerar, på vad hon agerar och varför hon vill det. att få leva som människa, kvinna, utan förtryck.”
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
ellen rase, sa18k
📸: @sonjamathews @mathewphoto

text: 🦋based on eckhart tolle’s philosophy he talks about the difference between inner peace and happiness. he points out that happiness is based on perceived conditions conditions that we perceive to be positive and inner peace is not. throughout the years during my practice i have come to realize that this is true and when you have inner peace you have it all because it does depend on what’s happening in the world in your experience but is in you already and is something that is powerful beyond belief.  #peace #peaceful #innerpeace #higherconsciousness #consciousness #mindfulness #mindfulness #laugh #loveyourself #innergrowth #awakening #healing #wcw #metoo #miami #boston #chicago #losangeles #newyork #newjersey #ecuador #peru #columbia #mexico

text:
brand new on the #playlist⠀
midnight creep by @professorplumbmusic⠀
⠀
no need to lock up your daughters when denver, colorado psychedelic metal four-piece professor plumb comes around. midnight creep is a rumbling, two minute heavy rock celebration of the #metoo movement, eschewing metal's history of chauvinism, self-indulgence and egotism. rightly characterising sexual predators in positions of power as monstrous creatures from the deep, this new track is accompanied by a video that ridicules donald trump, bill cosby and harvey weinstein, among others - creepy men, many from the entertainment industry, and those who defend them.⠀
⠀
full interview and lyric video - link in bio!!!!⠀
⠀
"if rock is dead anyway (right?), why not have a reset?" he continues. "why not be honest and say, 'yeah, so the old rockers made some great music but many of them were simply terrible human beings.' an unfortunate by-product of an industry with a very high ratio of people with narcissistic and borderline personality traits. so, i don't care if you wrote some hits...you're still an asshole!"⠀
⠀

text:
she’s one of my most favourite people – inspirational, kind, selfless, empowering, fearless, honest and optimistic – it wasn’t so long ago that robin nance started to get us thinking. from the fashion industry to hospitality, robin’s an all-around huge heart – and her presence fills the room before she gets through the door. robin’s honest; and i mean truly honest – i’ve seen her break down systems, personalities, characters and challenges like the new york times crossword. she says the things we’re all thinking.
.
.
she’s one of those professionals who embraces everything in her current and past, honestly, and gives those inspired by her, familiar moments to relate to. that’s why hospitality is so important to her, all the eccentric, the interesting and the artistic have found a home in the drinks industry, but there’s some work to do on how to find – and hold – your spot. “we have to be more inclusive. i work with bartenders every single day – and it just breaks my heart when i see bartenders making fun of people’s drink orders or of videos of bartenders they feel are ‘less than’. we should be lifting each other up. remember, it wasn’t long ago when bartending wasn’t considered a ‘real job’. we need to be gentle with each other, and ourselves.”
.
.
the impact that the drinks industry has on our everyday lives is more than cocktails, it’s about empowerment, and providing the shoulders for others to stand on. if you’re strong enough to be that person, and robin is, we can only imagine what’s possible for others. “i want to see more women and people of colour in positions of management and ownership.”
.
.
robin’s easy to spot in the crowd – bright red or pink hair (depending on the season), a larger than life personality, covered in tattoos with an energy and expression of generosity that blankets everything in sight. you’ll want to be in the vicinity, make friends, grab some rose and talk the afternoon away.
.
.
“not all those who wander are lost” says robin, remarking on her own journey that takes us to this moment. the return to real hospitality, and an exploration of one’s self is the real “wanderlust”, and she’s become quite good at it. #minibarleadingladies

text:
pro tip: fridays should always start with coffee and doughnuts.
___
if there's one thing i've learned about leading a team, it's that there's value in celebration and rewards. even in the small moments of progress, it's good to call attention to the things that move the needle forward. that push took energy, curiosity, and most importantly a permission to try despite the chance of failure.
___
raise your hand if you've ever been in the midst of growth and after about 5 minutes of not having 'grown' yet, you get impatient and judgmental of your process. listen, #metoo, so i want to remind you all that growth isn't a steep incline. it's peaks and pits, twists and turns, feeling off your rocker just as much as you feel on top of it, and tons of second guessing right before something amazing happens.
___
growth is unique in that way. progress is unique in that way. so why not celebrate every step of the way?
.
.
.
.
.
.
.

text:
no child should be abused 
its was a moment of empowerment at estate prinary school during our weekly advocacy and sensitization project towards creating a safer africa for the children
this week focused on children with special ability which experience various abuse as a result of their disabilities but we introduced
my body is my body programme - keeping children safe toward enable themnto know that their bodies are very special and nobody has the right to hurt nor torch them anyhow and need for them to report any action that's not making then uncomfortable to their parents and teachers.

thanks to the management and #teacher who use sign language to interprete the song to children who can't hear. however there's to support inclusive education for children with special ability in nigeria, africa.

together we can impact more lives

since 10/4 the dr set me free, from 5/9 when was on my toosh with a broken right foot. 
never realizing how much things really meant to me. loss comes in soooo many ways! losing my parents my bff’s, my sister and my career, was overwhelming & i allowed 
#grief & #depression to find a home, and it happens in a blink away. 
i spent time in the dark, finding myself even deeper than before, knowing who i am in this world and why i’m here....to live the best life, right here right now & be the best at what i do, because it comes naturally & organically.

text: fly like an eagle and soar on majestic wings. all things work together for good. team up with winners and people who fulfill their contracts, who deliver, who follow through on their word. keep your word, fulfill your contractual obligations and deliver on time-for budget. this year we found out that there are many people who say they can do and even sign contacts agreeing to do—but they can’t deliver. they are in breech of contract or they don’t return to you your property or goods. these people most likely will end up in bankruptcy or with a bad reputation. your reputation is everything you have. it can’t be bought. it can only be earned. if you don’t have money but you have an outstanding reputation, people will trust you and give you big contracts. guard your reputation. be sure that everything you do, you do with high integrity. deliver at all cost. this is how you build a long term business. this is how you create true influence. in a world where people can fake their instagram and hide their lawsuits, don’t disclose their bankruptcy, use nda’s to conceal their #metoo - its a sickness of our times. guard yourself: do background checks. guard your reputation. be transparent with your past. transparency leads to respect. find the good and trustworthy persons is the hard road but pays off in the end! #trust #compassion#trith #reputation #fashiontechnology #bethechange #bethechange #lessonslearned #backgroundcheck #smartbusiness #business #startup #starting #lessonslearnedinlife #lessonslearned #lessonoftheday photo by @lancemillerphotography for @alinecalledk #alinecalledk

text: right. i know hillary is liked by some dems but i don’t care. it’s exactly this sort of rhetoric from seemingly moderate politicians which fuels this sort of hatred. she is legitimising the idea that immigrants should not be allowed entry and giving it a platform, as if it is a genuinely acceptable idea that we, as the defenders of life and liberty, should cave to. the freedom loving peoples of europe should not and will not give into demands like this from the upper echelons of politics to pander to the far right. never. indeed, it is not the far right that needs to be protected from immigrants, but the immigrants that need to be protected from the far right, and that is what clinton and other self-proclaimed ‘liberals’ fail to understand. she should focus her attention on undermining the divisive and hateful message of the far right parties across europe and america, who themselves espouse disgusting policies like this, rather than taking some warped form of pragmatism to the extreme. coming from an immigrant family, i know what it’s like to face up to racism- overt, covert and everything in between. an american elite will not tell europe what to do, and i hope that those who love freedom continue to fight for it, and i hope that those who love peace continue to fight for the rights of refugees and immigrants all across the world. thank you for your service to the democratic party hillary, but it’s time you stepped back and knew when your time was over. now if this loses me some followers, so be it, but i will continue to fight for the democratic party in america so long as it fights for people like me, and people who need our protection- statements like this don’t do this. so hillary, in the name of your own beloved party, step back and let us take electoral defeat to the people you’re caving to in 2022.

in 2006, the ‘me too.’ movement was founded by tarana burke, and created to help survivors of sexual violence, predominantly with black women and girls, and other young women of color from low wealth communities, find their own pathways to healing. and what ignited this viral #metoo hashtag that consists of a viral conversation about sexual violence and has expanded into the national dialogue it now is, was the day tarana burke met a young girl named heaven. tarana burke had been a youth worker dealing predominately with black children and children of color, whom all came from different walks of life. during an all-girl bonding session at the youth camp tarana worked at, a young girl named heaven attended as she heard several girls in the room share very intimate stories that followed with the youth workers advising the girls to reach out to them if they ever needed to talk or needed help- and then they went their separate ways. however, the following day heaven had asked to speak to tarana privately, and when alone heaven began to vent about her painful stories of sexual violence she’d experienced with her mother’s boyfriend. horrified by the stories, tarana listened until she literally couldn’t could not take it anymore/ which had turned out to be less than 5 minutes.. unfortunately right in the middle of heaven sharing her pain with tarana, tarana cut her off and immediately directed her to another female counselor who could “help her better”, when in reality tarana connected to heaven’s pain and could feel her pain, yet couldn’t even bring herself to whisper...me too.
the ‘me too’ is a vision that works on building a community of advocates, driven by survivors, who will be at the forefront of creating solutions to interrupt sexual violence in their communities. and from what started as a grassroots work, has now expanded to reach a global community that helps de-stigmatize the act of surviving by highlighting the breadth and impact of sexual violence worldwide. the ultimate goal is to reframe and expand the global conversation around sexual violence and to disrupt the systems that allow for the global proliferation of sexual violence. #metoo

text:
stay in tune with who you are. today, i see so many women who are angry, unkind and just bitter at the world. i am a woman so i speak to women - let’s relax and lean in to who we truly are. it seems like the more freedom we get, the more unhappy we become. this just points to a deeper issue. 
as women, we have a lot of power. not the same way men have power but a power unique to women. a power that influences, shapes and makes better. 
breathe deep, control your emotions and offer a gentle word to someone in need today....it might just be your gentleness that will make a bigger difference than all the force in the world🍁☺️

text:
#fbf | a house on the ocean. december 1958. norma is writing on her red notebook. the playwright is working at his typewriter, under marilyn’s inquisitive watch. it’s norma who loves and wants him, not marilyn. as he goes out for a walk, marilyn chooses a few pages of the playwright’s script, and brings them to norma. “she can’t bear it that any man might look upon her without d-desire. she is thirty-two years old and fears that her youth is p-passing. she doesn’t get it, that she’s not going to m-make anybody h-happy. i feel… trapped.” norma throws them away, starts crying, then goes back to the pages: she starts tearing them apart one by one, and swallowing them. marilyn comforts her, taking her in her arms and prevents norma from chocking. 
i’m sorry, norma. i told you… he wasn’t trustworthy. 
with the playwright pouring his personal life into his work, she betrayed norma. but this time, she’s got marilyn by her side. 
_______________
