text:
when you feel that pull to say or do something and it is so strong that you think your heart might break in half if you don't do it, yeah, that is your purpose. follow that heart tug because that heart tug is where passion, purpose, and joy live. i have always loved writing. other than school research papers, i have kept my writing hidden. i love it so much that i was afraid if others saw my work and hated it, that it would break my heart past the point of repair. so i stayed in my comfort zone, which is public speaking, and wrote in secret. just a few years ago, my best friend introduced me to instagram. through my posts, i began forming my voice and developing my writing in shorter bursts. messages began flooding in from all over the world about how my posts touched people, helped people, made them think about something in a different way. over the past year, the pull to get my writing out there in a big way has become stronger and stronger. many nights of researching the how-tos and the platforms that speak to me. in early november, i posted my first ever article online titled "november elections: a nation of compassion fatigue." this article landed me my first freelance writing contract with komorebi post. in the last week i have published three articles with komorebi post. my articles are now trending as top stories! when you step into your light, warriors, you are a beacon for opportunity! people can't find you while you're settling. be brave and leap! ..
..
check out article in komorebi post on sex trafficking in the united states. you can also read my article by clicking the link in my bio ☝️
..
..
https://www.komorebipost.com/sold-in-america-sex-trafficking-united-states/

text_retweet:
recuerdos de cuando chimamanda ngozi adichie estuvo en el hay festival de gales en 2004. 15 años después vuelve con nosotros, al #haycartagena19

#repost from @hayfestival with @regram.app ... throwback to chimamanda ngozi adichie in hay back in 2004. she’s back in 2019, this time at our festival in colombia where she’ll be joined by zadie smith, yoko tawada, shirin ebadi, bianca jagger, sarah churchwell, doris salcedo and over 100 other inspiring writers, thinkers and performers.

this will be the festival’s 14th year in cartagena with writers and readers coming together to give voice to some of the biggest issues of our time; from climate change to migration, #metoo to #fakenews. meanwhile, award-winning performers will keep the show going until late.

follow @hayfestival_esp for updates through the year and explore the full programme online now.

#chimamandangoziadichie #writersofinstagram #hayfestival #haycartagena19 #literaryfestival #bookfestival #imaginetheworld #hayonwye #visitcartagena #visitcolombia

text:
#notme #dolceandgabbana #racism #boycott

hong kong - dolce & gabbana is facing a major crisis in china where top e-commerce sites are dumping its products over accusations of racism.

on social media, people posted videos of themselves burning the brand's clothes or cutting them into pieces and using them to wash their toilets.

thousands of d&g goods have disappeared from platforms run by companies like alibaba (baba) and jd.com (jd). the fashion house has faced intense anger after an instagram conversation in which gabbana described china as a “country of s***” was leaked.

many aren’t buying the excuse of hacking, pointing out that gabbana has a history of picking high-profile fights with multiple singers on instagram. gabbana has fought with elton john after making controversial remarks against vitro fertilization, called selena gomez “ugly,” and dismissed miley cyrus for critiquing his politics.

they’ve been accused of racially insensitive references in their work, such as describing gladiator-style sandals as “slave sandals” and featuring moorish — or “blackamoor” — imagery in a ready-to-wear collection. 
in one interview, they expressed their belief that “family” should be strictly defined as mother, father and naturally conceived children. they called ivf babies “synthetic” and said they didn’t support the right of gay parents to adopt.

gabbana has also questioned whether the #metoo movement exaggerates incidences of sexual harassment, and he maintains that sexual harassment is a nonissue in italy.

his pattern of picking fights might have gotten him in trouble here. chinese social media controversies can blow up overnight and many companies have come under fire, including apple and mercedes-benz, often with the state media penning op-eds encouraging the outrage. 
dolce & gabbana has also gotten in trouble with china in 2017 before for featuring migrant workers and sanitation staff in ads as well as run-down parts of beijing that didn’t promote a glamorous look for the country.

text:
#tinder! i'm sure you all know that's the walmart of human beings!
a place that makes you believe that if your relationship fails you still won't run out of options. 
sadly, it makes us just another commodity.

some will say it's just a platform to connect and take things forward, agreed. but is it fair to treat each other more like an options and swiping profiles just on the basis of face value. i tried it too, once. trust me, i made good friends. but i have also come across somethings that made me wonder, why people are seeking validation from those who hardly know you! 
i've had a break up where i was told that i'm playing victim, and that i went out and told people about stuff that should have stayed private. but tell me, why always talk and celebrate about the fake smile and pictures on social media and not the tough days that we face in relationships? 
i remember someone telling me that "tinder pe jp milte hain woh ek dusre ka khana h." joke it might sound, but can we believe that an app has created a market for people to pick one and drop one! 
relationships are tough, not all the pictures we see on facebook are just fairy tales, they too have their own share of struggles. but we don't see it coz they're committed to each other and love is forgiveness. commitment isn't easy in the age of tinder, coz it's a constant search of meeting people who will agree to our terms and conditions  and will live up to our generation's "go with the flow" wave. 
but since, we all have become so insensitive so insecure and so bloody stressed that all we want is runaway from relationships and ignore our flaws! i'm not against dating apps, but i'm really not in favour of filtering a relationship with set terms and conditions. 
#metoo
#mystory #share #bloggers #instaupload #scoopwhoop #relationshipquotes #relationships #speakup #changetheworld #onlinedating #datingapp

text:
female friday - simone biles is fierce--a hardworking, courageous, and talented woman.
-
born in columbus, ohio, she found her calling at a very early age. while attending a daycare field trip to a gymnastics centre, simone imitated the gymnasts and a coach spotted her natural ability. the coach sent a letter to simone's parents, urging them to let her join classes.
-
this was the beginning of simone's journey to becoming the first black female athlete to win gold in the all-around. with 19 olympic and world championship medals, she is the most decorated american gymnast in history. -
in 2018, simone became part of the #metoo movement when she bravely announced dr. larry nasser, former doctor for the u.s. national team, had sexually abused her. her story, along with the stories of over 150 other women he abused, helped convict nasser, who is currently serving a 100+ year life sentence.
-

text:
so this is a little life philosophy i have developed.

when i have conversations with friends about things they want from their life, but don't think they can have, this is what i say.

and it's basically explained by this. if you aren't pushing yourself, you aren't growing. have you heard the phrase, "nothing great ever came from comfort zones?" sure you can stick to what you've got, stay in that relationship that makes you unhappy, keep thinking everyone else are the ones who are causing the problems in your life, but you aren't living up to your true life path.

ive been through more difficult things than i would have ever imagined were meant for my life, but i did the hard work. i faced the things i didn't want to, and i've never been happier.

there are going to be some bad days by making that decision you have been putting off, but trust me, do the hard things in life and life will give you the good things you so deserve.

id love to hear one hard thing you did this year that you thought you never could, so comment below and tell me!

text:
▶️ table ronde sur le thème " la place des femmes dans le cinéma", organisé par le @fifb.official et animé par @deux_plus_un
▶️ vidéo 2 sur 3

avoir une sous-représentation des femmes dans un secteur comme le cinéma pose problème. pas seulement parce que 80% des films sont réalisés par des hommes, qu'ils détiennent les postes à responsabilités, qu'ils sont mieux payés et reçoivent les soutiens financiers les plus importants. pas seulement parce que les femmes sont tributaires de stéréotypes devant et derrière la caméra. cela pose problème parce que le cinéma façonne nos symboles, nourrit notre imaginaire collectif, transmet les perceptions de nos expériences sociales et culturelles différenciées. or, en 100 ans d’existence, la faible présence des femmes dans le cinéma, affadissant leurs vécus et leurs visions du monde, biaise pour nous tous et toutes la réalité. 
plus puissant que jamais au royaume des images, le 7ème art doit aujourd’hui permettre à chacun.e de s'identifier. c’est l’ambition que la magie du cinéma peut s’offrir.

merci à @annesserra, à @johannabros, à @@ferymalekmadani, à @myrnabhan, å marie vermeiren de @ellestournent et @lea_rogliardo de elles font des films. 
merci au festival international du film de bruxelles 2018

#fifb2018 #debat #lesfemmesdanslecinema #feminisme #laplacedesfemmes #femmesetart #femmesetculture #parité #agisme #racisme #minoritesinvisibles #quotasdefemmes #quotas #culture #societe #femmesetsociete #inegalitedeschances #metoo #deuxplusun #deuxplusunagency #cinéma #indistrieducinema #movie #womeninmovies

text:
▶️ table ronde sur le thème " la place des femmes dans le cinéma", organisé par le @fifb.official et animé par @deux_plus_un
▶️ vidéo 3 sur 3

avoir une sous-représentation des femmes dans un secteur comme le cinéma pose problème. pas seulement parce que 80% des films sont réalisés par des hommes, qu'ils détiennent les postes à responsabilités, qu'ils sont mieux payés et reçoivent les soutiens financiers les plus importants. pas seulement parce que les femmes sont tributaires de stéréotypes devant et derrière la caméra. cela pose problème parce que le cinéma façonne nos symboles, nourrit notre imaginaire collectif, transmet les perceptions de nos expériences sociales et culturelles différenciées. or, en 100 ans d’existence, la faible présence des femmes dans le cinéma, affadissant leurs vécus et leurs visions du monde, biaise pour nous tous et toutes la réalité. 
plus puissant que jamais au royaume des images, le 7ème art doit aujourd’hui permettre à chacun.e de s'identifier. c’est l’ambition que la magie du cinéma peut s’offrir.

merci à @annesserra, à @johannabros, à @@ferymalekmadani, à @myrnabhan, å marie vermeiren de @ellestournent et @lea_rogliardo de elles font des films. 
merci au festival international du film de bruxelles 2018

text: raising money and awareness for @_thedashcharity and white ribbon day on 25th november to put an end to #domesticabuse. caron has worked with dash for over 15 years and works so hard to raise awareness. i’m honoured to be an ambassador for dash and part of such an inspiring team who are dedicated to supporting those people that really need it. it was so touching to see people donating in #windsor today who had been helped by dash in the past. they provide help and support to those suffering all types of domestic abuse from family members. their stories are heartbreaking and their work is desperately needed. we need donations to keep going - we are a small charity and depend on your donations to keep going. if you can donate today please do as it will go straight to helping those in need. https://www.paypal.com/gb/fundraiser/charity/131157 is the link and can be found in the bio for @_thedashcharity too. #everylittlehelps #charity #makeadonation #metoo #ambassador

text_retweet:
✊🏾🙏🏾 #repost @onubrasil
・・・
artigo: salvemos a vida das mulheres na américa latina — uma mudança de mentalidade (por izumi nakamitsu, representante das @nacoesunidas para assuntos de desarmamento)
•
a igualdade entre homens e mulheres continua sendo um assunto pendente. o movimento #metoo colocou a atenção internacional na prevalência generalizada da agressão sexual e do assédio.

a verdade é que a violência contra mulheres e meninas é uma das violações de direitos humanos mais comuns, arraigadas e devastadoras do mundo.

em muitos lugares, essa violência é parte da vida cotidiana, é uma ameaça constante apoiada em noções destrutivas de masculinidade e que dá forma às interações humanas.

o machismo está presente na vida cotidiana da américa latina, apesar de não ser exclusivo dessa região. esta noção arcaica de masculinidade, em conjunto com a ampla disponibilidade de armas de fogo, é uma receita para aqueles que se sentem no direito de exercer poder sobre outros.

nos lares e entre parceiros, o poder das armas para ameaçar e aterrorizar faz com que atos como assédio e estupro sejam fáceis de serem cometidos pelos abusadores. os perpetuadores atacam cotidianamente indivíduos por meses e anos, e seus crimes só são interrompidos com a morte de suas vítimas.

a américa latina abriga 14 dos 25 países onde o feminicídio é mais comum. doze assassinatos motivados por gênero ocorrem na região a cada dia, a maioria por meio de armas de fogo, e as leis não garantem justiça para 49 de cada 50 vítimas.

ao lembrar o dia internacional para a eliminação da violência contra a mulher, 25 de novembro, começamos com 16 dias de ativismo contra a violência de gênero, nos quais as pessoas da região compartilham a responsabilidade de pressionar para colocar fim a esses atos e atitudes culturais que a tornam possível. como disse minha colega, amina mohammed, secretária-geral adjunta das nações unidas, “nenhuma mulher deve morrer por ser mulher”.
•
nos últimos anos, foi firmada uma série de compromissos internacionais para combater a violência de gênero. mencionarei três deles. (continua nos comentários)

text:
you want to be clear on your boundaries, but for most of your life you didn’t know what they were, or that you were even allowed to have them.

you want to experience deep intimacy in life, but you’re all too familiar with the feeling of losing yourself in relationship with another person. 
you want to show up powerfully in your relationships, but struggle to communicate what you truly want, need and feel in the moment.

you are passionate about being a vehicle for positive change in the world, and want your relationships to support you in your growth and expansion.

as we become more empowered and free in our relationships, we need to cultivate clear boundaries, so that as we open up our hearts in connection with another, we do not give ourselves away in the process. 
i know you, because i am you, and i've created a course to walk us through the process of remembering who we are.

the soul of boundaries is a user manual for creating deeper alignment between who we truly are and how we show up in our relationships. 
it is a guide for identifying the underlying belief systems, emotions, and energetics that get in the way of us connecting to and communicating our yes and no in the moment.

this course is usually $97, however, as a black friday weekend special, the course cost is on $37 now through monday (11/26) at midnight!

here is the link to learn more and purchase the course: www.ariellebrown.com/boundaries

text:
⚠️trigger warning if: you have cocsa ptsd, csa trama, or experienced or are a survivor and/or victim of sexual assault or abuse⚠️
#poetrycommunity #photography #poetry #csa #personal #metoo #spokenwordpoetry 
the first time someone showed their body to me sexually i dont remember it. i was too young, my dad said.
the first time i got called jailbail was when i was in middle school.
the first time i experienced sexting i was 12, first time recieving a nude was 11, first time sending one i was 13- please dont ask how old they were it won't make any of this better i promise.

the first time someone entered this body without my consent i was 15. he keep trying to reassure me, he was a friend,  i could trust him right? and while i stopped him, he wouldnt stop with my best friend, i found out.

i remember since elementary school people touching parts of my body that werent theirs and somehow down the line those parts werent mine either.

the second and third time someone violated this body, he was a boyfriend. i kept saying i didnt want it and no matter how lifeless my body was he wouldnt stop, he claims it was to make me feel better- dont call it that word theyll say, be lucky it was only his hands and mouth.

the forth time someone used this body for themselves was a guy in the back of his car and he wouldnt stop pulling my head back down. 
a famous activist once said how as an adult he had to come to the realization that his body was his and not something he inhabited that other people did things to

the fifth time someone took my body from me, he was a friend and we had a good night out so the sleepiness agreed to spend the night and it wouldve been a sixth and seventh in that one night had i not fought back. i felt the pain of the tear for a week.

babygirl, there are people in this world who will betray your trust and make your body feel alien, dont let that stop you from reclaiming this gift from the gods as yours
and always remember no one can take you without your permission.

they didnt bite off pieces of your home 
they betrayed god in the garden.

did you know? 
anjaneyasana - low lunge variations stretch and opens up the thighs, groin, (sciatica) and chest.  it is great for athletes 
and those of us who sit for long periods of time. 
driving for hours, sitting for hours, maybe your a 
runner 🏃‍♀️ or a bike rider 🚵🏽‍♀️ rock climber 🧗🏾‍♀️or whatever you do, your flexibility is 👎🏼 join me for yoga 🧘🏻‍♂️ & let me show you how..... @@@@@@@

text:
i was having a conversation with a man yesterday, actually i was listening to him speak about his life. how for the first part he was in the war and the second half he was an engineer. and now, at 70 years old he knows there’s something more than his logical mind. there’s something more than the linear life he’s lived where everything is white or black where he crossed all the t’s and dotted all the i’s. 💛
i began to take him down the journey of the palm trees, how shallow its roots are and how we could perceive it as not being grounded. and yet if we took a really good look at it and allow ourselves to feel its beauty. how its leaves flow so free, feel its grandeur and how majestic it is. we can easily get mesmerized by the beauty of its essence. 💛
as he looked at me, nodding, i knew he understood. we always have choices i said. and these are the little moments of beauty we can continue to seek, or we can continue to wish we had stopped living life with blinders on. he thanked me and went on his way.
💛
a beautiful young man once told me, no regrets momzy, never have regrets! it’s all experiences 💛
today i tell you, no regrets beautiful people, never have regrets! it’s all experiences
💛
what matters is your next choice! let your heart listen and your soul speak. 💛
what will you choose today?

text:
jeg ligger i en blomstereng og ser opp i evigheten. pleddet jeg har med i sekken, gir meg en liten firkantet tomt her inne, og ingen kan se meg fra stien. sykkelen står oppreist mot en stor stein, og frister kanskje eventuelle kleptomane som kommer forbi. dagen er av den varme sorten, og jeg ligger her svett og varm etter å ha klatret en litt brattere omvei en vanlig. mitt «hemmelige hus» eksisterer kun i juni måned hvert år, mens de knallgule bakkesoleiene strekker seg som heftigst mot himmelen. jeg ligger her å tenker på hva som gjør meg glad, og hva jeg gjør når jeg trives og er helt oppslukt. jeg tenker på hva som er viktig i livet, og jeg tenker på at jeg bare har ett liv, og kun en mulighet til å realiser meg selv. denne opplevelsen fra sist sommer, er et av mine kjæreste minner. alene med naturen tok jeg et valg. jeg bestemte meg for å gi de samme rådene til meg selv, som jeg gir til andre. jeg bestemte meg for å være stolt av meg selv, og aldri mer føle skam på grunn av overgrepene i barndommen. jeg innså at det er de som tør å skille seg ut som forandrer verden... 😅🚴‍♀️💨
.

name: Heidi Irene Arstad
tweet_full:
jeg ligger i en blomstereng og ser opp i evigheten. pleddet jeg har med i sekken, gir meg en liten firkantet tomt her inne, og ingen kan se meg fra stien. sykkelen står oppreist mot en stor stein, og frister kanskje eventuelle kleptomane som kommer forbi. dagen er av den varme sorten, og jeg ligger her svett og varm etter å ha klatret en litt brattere omvei en vanlig. mitt «hemmelige hus» eksisterer kun i juni måned hvert år, mens de knallgule bakkesoleiene strekker seg som heftigst mot himmelen. jeg ligger her å tenker på hva som gjør meg glad, og hva jeg gjør når jeg trives og er helt oppslukt. jeg tenker på hva som er viktig i livet, og jeg tenker på at jeg bare har ett liv, og kun en mulighet til å realiser meg selv. denne opplevelsen fra sist sommer, er et av mine kjæreste minner. alene med naturen tok jeg et valg. jeg bestemte meg for å gi de samme rådene til meg selv, som jeg gir til andre. jeg bestemte meg for å være stolt av meg selv, og aldri mer føle skam på grunn av overgrepene i barndommen. jeg innså at det er de som tør å skille seg ut som forandrer verden... 😅🚴‍♀️💨
.

text:
since the other night was a bit triggering, i was debating about what to post next.
.
do i make things light again? or do i let you see a bit more of my past?
.
i realize i’m covered in scars, beautiful scars, and maybe it’s time to share the darker sides of my life.
.
but...i hope you all see that you can be scarred and still shine.
.
you will smile again. you will find yourself again. then one day, you will love again. .
all in time, loves.
.
.
.

text: when we think of superheroes, we think of a @marvel inspired action figure with a cape & super human powers ⚡️but to me, the true superheroes are the ordinary people doing extraordinary things. long before the #metoo movement, my aunty andy did what many, especially from my culture & country south africa, dared not to do by putting rape & gender based violence in the spotlight & breaking the silence by saying enuf is enuf - which became the slogan for her foundation, kwanele. yesterday it was announced that she had won a landmark case against south africa’s minister of police & south african police service who failed her & so many others by not investigating their cases properly. 8 long years, never giving up to achieve this victory for all. she took her pain & brokenness & turned it into powder with purpose. she endured the whispers & scrutiny, sadly often by other women in our “so called” community. “what was she doing there in the first place on her own?” i’ve heard people ask. i’m sorry, i wasn’t aware that going for a walking on the beach in broad daylight at 2.30pm was a criminal offence? 🤬 nothing can ever justify or explain the horrific nature of what happened to her. it breaks my heart that my beautiful south africa has become known as the ‘rape capital of the world’. that just today i was reading about a 7 year old who went to the toilet in a restaurant & was raped. i also read about victims as young as 6 weeks old! sadly, stories like these and aunty andy’s have unfortunately become common place around the world. an initial reaction of shock, disbelief and anger and then nothing - on to the next news story. i was conflicted whether to share this post. i realised the true conflict was about the conspiracy of silence about rape, sexual violence & abuse, especially in bame communities. well enuf is enuf! i will not be complicit in the silence any longer! the kwanele! enuf is enuf! aim is to ‘break the chain of silence protecting rape and sexual violence - and their perpetrators’ by taking a ‘continuous and pro-active stand against these crimes. so with that i want to honour and acknowledge the petite power house that is andy kawa #superwoman

text:
i love these words. they remind me of the lightness i felt on wednesday morning, the morning after sending off that accountability request statement and reading it out loud. the next morning i felt high. i felt energized. i felt clear. i felt present. i felt as if i’d just shed a hundred pounds. i felt unburdened.

and i’m using past tense because today i’m not feeling quite so high as i recognize there are still some “incompletes” on my end to handle, and perhaps more truth to be told without being so vague. but i do feel a shift. and it feels good. so i’m breathing into that... for now i just want to enjoy the relief and the afterglow of tuesday night’s labor before addressing those other things. the bulk of my work here is done. the burden of responsibility is now mostly where it belongs, and that is not with me. 
#truth #freedom #peace

text:
tw: sexual assault 
a few weeks ago when taking a stroll in assistens cemetery in copenhagen, i came across this tomb. and these words.

a wave of sadness and empathy submerged me. was it a relative, a friend, a neighbour? was writing #metoo on their tomb a way to get heard? or get some sort of justice? did they hang this stuff elephant because it happen to them as a child? did they die before they could challenge them for what they did? or maybe they realised the gravity of what happened after they died?

but most importantly, i prayed for this person to get the support they need to heal. 
seeing this hurt me deep, so deep. #metoo is so important as a movement - yet these constant reminders of the violence women face  in this world is tough. processing all these triggers is emotionally exhausting. i try to deal with my own pain yet there is always something to remind me of it. 
so much that it took me weeks to get the strength to post this picture. but it's probably not nearly as much strength it took this person to speak up.

text:
men who are full of hate love to pretend to care about women when it suits their agenda. 
for generations women's experiences of sexual assault have been rebranded to fit different narratives of hate. 
i reject the invocation of white womanhood to justify racism. i reject the use of women's pain to further a hateful agenda.
anyone who shouts "look over there" rather than tackling the root causes of sexual violence doesn't care about women.
women need to stop falling for this bullshit, the revolution will be intersectional.

text:
#نوستالژی_سیاسی #انتخابات_هاشمی#۸۴
سال هشتاد چهار بود اوج انتخابات کروبی ساسی مانکن آورده بود #رشت چه جنجالی شد #دلواپسان نگذاشتن طرف را به قول ما رشتی ها به دو دادن .
من آن زمان ریس اجرایی ستاد دانشجویی مرحوم #هاشمی بودم ستاد مرکزی از ما خواست برای شور انتخابات یکی رو بیاریم رشت تا جوان ها یه حالی بکنن از ستادبانوان هاشمی تماس گرفتند که ما میتونیم #مریم_دیجی را بیاریم رشت ولی کلیه امنیت و آماده سازی با شما من هم قبول کردم خلاصه آن شب تیم ما تاصبح بیدار بود تا ورزشگاه #عضدی_رشت را البته سالن سرپوشیده ویژه بانوان آماده کنیم #دلواپسان و #نگران شونده ها هر کاری کردند نتوانستند جلو برنامه را بگیرند خلاصه ما بعد مدتی #خط_قرمز  را در آن سال رد کردیم البته پشتمونم به مرحوم #هاشمی گرم بود ولی نکته اینجاست که تمام جان ما دادیم کنسرت خانم ها دیدن ما فقط بو کشیدیم . و دیگه همچین اتفاقی در رشت که نه در گیلان که نه در ایران نیوفتاده.

text:
a thing i wrote on the feeling of 
failure 
neon lights 
blaring in my mind 
hides
they won’t see this broken girl inside 
hurting me 
hunting me 
every night 
and every day
failing
less than enough 
not enough 
never enough 
unworthy of love
scared quartz veins in a gold loving world
silence
head spinning 
mind reeling 
disproportionate unfeeling
a precarious silver needle 
perched on delicate claws
threading my lips together 
silence
what we see we do not choose 
all we can choose is change 
rip the stiches from our mouths 
and tell the world we breathe

“i could lie, say i like it like that, like it like that”

i’ve been thinking about my assault and rape a lot lately. how i’ve allowed it to affect my life the way it has. i’ve been thinking of my abusive relationship a lot lately. how i’ve allowed it to affect my life the way it has. how i’ve become the person i am today because of it. how sometimes it’s hard for me to speak when i’m uncomfortable out of fear of being hit. how i tend to allow discomfort during sexual encounters out of fear of another black eye. how it’s hard to love significant others out of fear of being left used and broken. how i’ve lost my voice when i’m scared. how i over react when i can’t explain feelings. how i am not the same bubbly, happy, fun loving girl i used to be. i say “sad gurl” for this@specific reason. my smile might always be there, but deep down i am hurting, afraid to make the next move, dying inside wondering what makes anyone else different from the ones who hurt me. i cringe at certain smells and names. i cry due to certain acts of pleasure. i live every day of my life, fearful and sad because two men thought it was okay to take my body as their own. #metoo #youarenotalone #rapevictim #rapesurvivor #rapesurvivorsstandup #domesticviolence #domesticviolencesurvivor #domesticviolenceawarness #rapecultureisreal

text:
so i usually avoid the thankful thanksgiving posts because they tend to just get lost in a sea of food pics and family photos, but this year i have to take a second to reflect and share.

2018 has been the absolute worst year of my life. i had to walk away from my dream job at a place that held my heart to pursue the betterment of my own mental, physical, and emotional health. i went full time working a job that, on most days, feels like i'm compromising in the worst way possible, but has given me the ability to continuously work toward a place of financial freedom. i faced the great car saga of 2k18, which still feels like an ongoing battle of wits, duct tape, zip ties, and praying the darn thing won't fall into a million pieces on the freeway. i was violated in the worst way i had never thought possible. "that will never happen to me" suddenly becomes #metoo. i had a major health scare that suddenly put words like 'biopsy' and 'cancer' in my vocabulary. i faced the frustration, bitterness, and heartache that can come from parenting your parents. i've felt trapped in my own mind, body, and life circumstances. i've felt abandoned. broken. alone. 
and yet, i look at where i'm at right in this moment, and i am thankful. i am thankful that, even though i have felt the gut-wrenching pit of loneliness in my heart at times, i know the incredible tribe i surround myself with will always be there through every life situation, every weird distant phase and crazy schedule, with nothing but love and patience. i am thankful for my little home, my peaceful place of freedom that i had to fight for, but emerged victorious. i am thankful to be a fighter. i am thankful for the god given ability (albeit not always an easy one to put into practice...) to replace hate and bitterness and pain and anger with love, understanding, and inner peace. in moments of darkness, it's not always easy to maintain a thankful mindset, but when i look at everything i have been blessed with, i have to remind myself of how far i've come, and that i'm not done yet. i'm a work in progress, a dark sky that has weathered some storms, but will never stop looking for her rainbow.

text:
author of those words, doctor george tiller, was murdered by so-called “pro-life” people. isn’t it outrageous? so often we repeat here that “pro-lifers” are not truly respecting life, and this is one of the most gruesome examples of it. ⠀
⠀
if you want to learn more about doctor tiller and his coworkers, watch “after tiller” documentary - amazing, eye-opening piece. about very emotional subject: third-trimester abortions. ⠀
⠀
it taught me a lot about people who make those decisions, in what situations, and how much help they need. and those doctors - one of the most carrying human beings i’ve ever saw. truly being there where they are needed so much. ⠀

text:
i loved this person whole heartedly, wanted to marry him, and we would be together the rest of our lives. or at least i thought i did. but when i saw red flags that pushed my boundaries that were not ok i asked nicely to go our separate ways but remain friends. i never expected in a million years what he did and put me through would end up happening and still continues. 
people wear masks, people act certain ways to get what they want, people play the victim to make you feel bad about your boundaries. a year and 8 months. how long it took to see a monster after getting put in a cage mentally and physically. mental abuse is a bitch. physical abuse is a bitch. sexual abuse is a bitch. my goal and hope is to stop this person from ever doing this to another person again. i will not be silenced, will not back down, or be put through fear. thank you for showing me the weaknesses within myself. thank you for revealing you are a terrible human being. thank you for showing me i deserve better and my expectations are not out of reach. thank you, next. 
#abuse #sexualabuse #mentalabuse #physicalabuse #metoo #thankyounext #love #trust #relationships #abuseawareness #selflove #takecareofyourself #lovethyselffirst #loveyourself

text:
➡️ @doodleodrama
.
one of you recently shared your horrifying experience with me
.
this lady was continuously harassed/molested by a group of men when she was a teenager. they used to follow her to the bus stop and then continue to elbow, pinch, grab, nudge her throughout the ride. it lasted an entire year almost. she was just 13 at the time and too scared to speak up. she never spoke up. eventually it stopped, she grew up, moved cities, moved jobs, got married but the incident stayed with her. she often thinks about it and the what ifs. .
.
i feel grateful and blessed that my work allows people to open up and share their experiences with me but at the same time i feel helpless too. there’s nothing i can do to make this woman forget that horrible episode. there’s no way i can travel back in time and protect that 13 year old kid. but i sincerely hope that all of you reading this learn to be more vigilant and alert. not all of us are strong enough to speak up. try and be a voice to those who need a little helping finding their own :)
.
.
.
.
.
source: @theawarians
.
.
.
.
.

text:
#thegregwilson 
i had some friends in town and they were headed to the sycamore tavern on sunset, just east of labrea. upstairs there's a private room.  they host various comedy nights, including the one i went to called the dojo of comedy. in my opinion, mr. greg romero wilson, aka the greg wilson, stole the show. from start to finish, he nailed it. he didn't avoid tough subjects either. his jokes had no bounds as he touched upon suicide and the #metoo movement, yet he did so with comedic precision, impeccable timing, all with a hilarious and well executed delivery. i dont normally do the selfie fan boy thing, but in this i went up to greg to congratulate him on a flawless set. he was as polite as he was funny. i didn't post this pic until now because i couldn't remember his name, or find the flyer. i saw him yesterday on a progressive commercial with flo where he is her jungle guide. greg's website says "give greg a damn special," and i must admit, he deserves one! i'd watch it... #wolfmanraymond #wolfmanpresents #gregromerowilson #grw #gregwilson #givegregadamnspecial #progressive #jungletourguide #jungleguide #progessivecommercial #flo #sycamore #sycamoretavern #thedojo #thedojocomedy #thedojoofcomedy #comedian #funnymofo #hollywood #blogger #comedygold #comedyclub #sunset #sunsetblvd #whydoilookfunny

thankyou everyone.

text:
in the world where everyday begins with a new #metoo story, 
in the world where often an innocent is being accused for  crime they didn't commit, 
in the world gaining sympathy by false stories becomes standards, 
in the world where people fight for equality, 
in the world where equality is long forgotten, 
in the world where women forget that men can be innocent too, 
in that world i want to stand by those innocent men who are pin pointed for being true, 
in that world i want to support all those brothers and fathers who not only protect their own sisters and daughters but also protect each and every strange girl they'll meet, 
in that world i want to establish respect for those men who deserve to be respected,
in that world i want to create another small world where equality refers equality for all and not feminism, 
in that world i wish to create a world of humanity and love. ©harshita ashwani

in the world where equality is long forgotten, 
in the world where women forget that men can be innocent too, 
in that world i want to stand by those innocent men who are pin pointed for being true, 
in that world i want to support all those brothers and fathers who not only protect their own sisters and daughters but also protect each and every strange girl they'll meet, 
in that world i want to establish respect for those men who deserve to be respected,
in that world i want to create another small world where equality refers equality for all and not feminism, 
in that world i wish to create a world of humanity and love. ©harshita ashwani

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

established in 1999 by the un general assembly, the day against violence against women was set for november 25 of each year.
this is our tribute to the most beautiful part of the human beings.
the women, who mankind create it, love it and save it.
ours is a simple but sincere tribute, ironic but subtle, strong but kind.
those who use violence against women are a coward.
those who mistreat women are ... an asshole!
with love

angelo and andrea

text:
fullmånen har släppt sitt grepp. sömnen infann sig äntligen efter en väldigt bra, annorlunda, rolig, sorglig, tänkvärd föreställning i malmö igårkväll. mia skäringers no more fucks to give. jag önskar att fler män hade följt med sina kvinnor. för det vi kvinnor,  födda under 50-60-70-talet,  varit med om förstår faktiskt inte alla män. de tysta övertrampen och sexuella ”skämten” på jobbet. den självklara (för en del män) tystnaden från kvinnorna som ändå tycker synd om männen som burit sig åt. det var väl ändå lite mitt fel också. väl. men nej. nu är det stopp. #metoo fick oss att bli modiga, våga berätta, sluta acceptera dumheter, träda fram och försvara oss själva. föreställningen var viktig. jätteviktig. jag känner att inte förrän nu vid 54 års ålder, då jag om en vecka gifter mig med en jämlik respektfull, klok snäll, stabil och omtänksam man, har jag hunnit ifatt mig själv och mina sår sen 30-40 år tillbaka börjar läka. ärren finns där men idag är de bara en påminnelse om att nya generationer ska med klar röst våga säga nej eller för den skull ja. vi har alla en viktig uppgift att bryta negativa mönster och vi ser resultatet i våra barn som inte ens förstår vad jag pratar om. de har fått en helt annan världsbild där vi är rädda om varandra, jämlikhet är självklart och ett nej är alltid ett nej. 
jag tankar citrontarterna fulla med glädje och jävlar anamma idag. vi inledde pink weekend igår och det var så mysigt att ni kom och fikade en helt vanlig fredag mitt i ingenstans i mitt lavendelblå villavillerkulla. idag bjuder vi på räkmacka och kaffe när du handlar för 500kr. man blir ju hungrig av att fynda och julhandla. varmt välkommen till oss 12-16 lördag och söndag. #reunionhome #reunionhomeandfriends #pinkweekend #inredningsbutik #doftverkstad #fika #gärsnäs #österlen

text:
▪ma pensée à toutes les femmes issues des zones des conflits armés et dans les pays où les violances de toites sorte contre les femmes sont monai courante.
▪au moment où les femmes rwandaises rescapées du génocide ont toujours des cicatrices des violances subies, les femmes congolaises, sud-sudanaises, centrafricaines, somaliennes, nigerianes, syriennes, yéménites,... subissent les violances despuis plusieurs décennies aux yeux de tous. elles attendent impatiemment que la justice soit de leur côté.
▪je pensse encore à celles qui ne sont pas à l'abri dans les camps des déplacés et aux camps des réfugiés, à celles qui n'ont pas d'abri et sont à la merci de toit les malfaiteurs dans la rue, plus particulièrement aux sdf de paris que je croise tout les jours.
▪je pense à celles issues des pays pauvres qui espèrent sauver leur famille avec un travail de misère en atabie saoudite, ce pays de plusieurs fous qui font subir à ces pauvres femmes toutes les violences que tout être humain a peur de subir. ces femmes jusqu'aujourd'hui appellent à l'aide, mais le monde entier reste silencieux, puisque leurs intérêts sont prioritaires. les grandes puissance ont besoins de faire tourner leurs industries d'armement et d'aviation. le monde entier devait avoir honte.
▪je pense à tiutes ces femmes qui sont obligées de subir puisqu'on leur fait comprendre qu'autrement leur carrière est en danger.
▪je pense à toutes les journalistes, politiciennes, activistes de droit de l'hommes du monde entier qui ont accepté de subir les violances de toutes sortes pour défendre les intérêts des peuples démunis.
▪merci à tous les hommes qui rejoignent notre cause, un grand merci à dr mukwege, le reparateur des corps des femmes déchirées par la guerre à l'est de la rdc.

que la justice soit faite a toutes les femmes sans aucune distinction.

lucie umukundwa, créatrice d'izuba gallery

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

text:
i started working on something new yesterday: a project centred on a found object, in this case a book of photography from the 1970’s, featuring sexualised imagery of incredibly young women.  the esteemed photographic artist in question is of no importance; his moment in the spotlight is over.  it is not my place to affirm or deny the allegations of sexual abuse and rape of children directed at him.  as a society we spend way too much time obsessing about (alleged) perpetrators anyway and not nearly enough time listening to the (alleged) victims.  but i cannot wash my hands of clean of this either, so i am left to deal with it all in the only means i know how – by making art. . 
this is a work in progress – more to follow.
.
.
.
.
#photography #art #visualart #timebasedart #intermedia #conceptualart #workinprogress #artoftheday #artofinstagram #contemporaryart #instaart #artist #visualartist #foundobject #metoo
